t%20have%20been%20programmatically%20reuploading%20content%20from%20smaller%20accounts%20to%20game%20the%20revenue%20share%20program%20and%20circumvent%20crediting%20the%20original%20author.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWe%20are%20now%20identifying%20these%20posts%20and%20allocating%20the%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20Nikita%20Bier%20(%40nikitabier)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fnikitabier%2Fstatus%2F2058020001823793265%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMay%2023%2C%202026%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EBier%20said%20X%20is%20now%20identifying%20those%20posts%20and%20%26quot%3Ballocating%20the%20impressions%20entirely%20to%20the%20creator%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20effort%20aimed%20at%20making%20sure%20original%20posters%20%E2%80%94%20not%20aggregators%20%E2%80%94%20get%20paid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20posts%20with%20added%20commentary%2C%20Bier%20recommended%20using%20X's%20%26quot%3BShare%20Video%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BQuote%26quot%3B%20feature%20to%20ensure%20attribution%20goes%20to%20the%20original%20creator.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20is%20part%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fx-product-head-nikita-bier-playbook-get-rich-posting-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebroader%20push%20by%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20reduce%20payouts%20for%20aggregators%2C%20whose%20business%20model%20has%20often%20depended%20on%20rapidly%20repackaging%20other%20people's%20work%20for%20monetizable%20engagement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBier%20singled%20out%20one%20of%20the%20platform's%20most%20prolific%20posters%20on%20Saturday.%20Mario%20Nawfal%20is%20the%20CEO%20of%20IBC%20Group%2C%20a%20crypto%20consulting%20firm.%20He%20also%20hosts%20the%20largest%20live%20discussion%20show%20on%20X%20and%20has%20some%203.5%20million%20followers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENawfal%20reposted%20a%20video%20of%20an%20ABC%20News%20journalist%20reacting%20to%20gunshots%20fired%20outside%20the%20White%20House%20on%20Saturday.%20A%20community%20note%20below%20the%20post%20now%20reads%2C%20%26quot%3BOP%20stole%20this%20video%20without%20providing%20credit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPlease%20do%20not%20reupload%20the%20author's%20video%3A%20use%20Quote%20or%20Video%20Reshare%2C%26quot%3B%20Bier%20added.%20%26quot%3BYour%20revenue%20was%20reduced%20by%2090%25%20last%20cycle%20and%20we're%20running%20out%20of%20room%20to%20reduce%20it%20more.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENawfal%20replied%20that%20his%20account%20always%20uses%20the%20video%20reshare%20option%2C%20but%20it%20doesn't%20work%20for%20longer%20tweets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20response%20now%20also%20has%20a%20community%20note%3A%20%26quot%3BNo%20he%20doesnt.%20Here%20are%20additional%20examples%20just%20from%20the%20last%20few%20hours%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20note%20says%2C%20listing%20three%20other%20posts%20that%20don't%20provide%20credit.%20%26quot%3BChronic%20content%20thief.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fx-cracks-down-on-stolen-content-nikita-bier-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1779648653000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a133ee77ff506e273e67558%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fx-cracks-down-on-stolen-content-nikita-bier-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22X's%20head%20of%20product%2C%20Nikita%20Bier%2C%20says%20the%20platform%20is%20moving%20to%20protect%20its%20creator%20revenue%20share%20program%20from%20users%20who%20steal%20original%20content.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lvaranasi%40businessinsider.com%20(Lakshmi%20Varanasi)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20gave%20my%20kids%20more%20responsibility%20at%20the%20grocery%20store.%20They%20rose%20to%20the%20challenge.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223060%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kids%20checking%20out%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a01faa7ba7ef34b41f3700a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222295%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20lets%20her%20kids%20check%20out%20at%20the%20supermarket.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI%20let%20my%20kids%20take%20over%20the%20grocery%20self-checkout.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhat%20started%20as%20chaos%20turned%20into%20teamwork%20and%20independence.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGrocery%20shopping%20became%20a%20way%20to%20teach%20practical%20life%20skills.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20always%20loved%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-tips-buying-cheap-groceries-for-big-family%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrocery%20shopping%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20my%20kids.%20From%20the%20time%20they%20were%20babies%20and%20toddlers%2C%20I%20loved%20putting%20them%20in%20the%20cart%20and%20chatting%20about%20what%20I%20was%20buying.%20It%20always%20feels%20a%20bit%20chaotic%2C%20but%20it's%20always%20been%20one%20of%20my%20favorite%20things%20to%20do%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20they're%20older%20and%20have%20graduated%20from%20riding%20in%20the%20cart%20to%20walking%20beside%20it%2C%20I've%20looked%20for%20ways%20to%20get%20them%20more%20involved%20in%20the%20process.%20They%20would%20help%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkids-grocery-shopping-alone-independence-confidence-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echoose%20produce%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20grab%20things%20off%20the%20shelf%20and%20put%20them%20in%20the%20cart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20then%20the%20day%20came%20when%20they%20wanted%20to%20start%20scanning%20groceries%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-i-stopped-using-self-checkout-for-human-connection-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20self-checkout%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There%20are%20three%20of%20them%2C%20and%20the%20thought%20of%20them%20all%20grabbing%20items%20out%20of%20the%20cart%20and%20scrambling%20to%20scan%20things%20seemed%20like%20%3Cem%3Ea%20lot%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20one%20day%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20the%20heck%2C%20let's%20see%20what%20happens.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225e61ab47-43e4-42c3-9af4-2ab759da7bb3%5C%22%3EThings%20got%20wild%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20time%20we%20did%20this%2C%20it%20was%20understandably%20chaotic.%20My%20son%20(the%20oldest)%20insisted%20on%20scanning%2C%20and%20the%20younger%20girls%20wanted%20to%20scan%20as%20well%2C%20so%20there%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20grabbing%20for%20items%20and%20running%20from%20the%20cart%20to%20the%20scanner.%20Groceries%20were%20tossed%20haphazardly%20in%20bags.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20trying%20to%20keep%20track%20and%20make%20sure%20everything%20was%20actually%20scanned%2C%20and%20one%20kid%20started%20looking%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-store-halloween-candy-2018-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecandy%20shelf%3C%2Fa%3E%20near%20the%20checkout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20left%2C%20I%20was%20sweating.%20But%20the%20kids%20were%20so%20happy.%20You'd%20think%20they%20had%20just%20gotten%20to%20drive%20a%20spaceship.%20But%20no%2C%20they%20literally%20did%20a%20basic%20grown-up%20task%20that%20many%20actually%20dread.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fdc3738e-85fc-41df-9ca4-fe62305d0092%5C%22%3EThey%20fell%20into%20their%20own%20roles%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20few%20times%2C%20they%20fell%20into%20a%20rhythm%20that%20I%20had%20no%20hand%20in%20figuring%20out.%20Each%20started%20to%20handle%20their%20own%20task%20while%20I%20kept%20a%20watchful%20eye%20on%20the%20cart%20and%20made%20sure%20everything%20got%20scanned.%20The%20oldest%20and%20the%20middle%20work%20on%20scanning%2C%20even%20talking%20to%20each%20other%20to%20make%20sure%20nothing%20is%20left%20behind%2C%20or%20adjusting%20based%20on%20who%20can%20pick%20it%20up%20(my%20son%20takes%20care%20of%20the%20heavier%20items).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20item%20is%20scanned%2C%20it's%20passed%20to%20the%20little%20one%2C%20who%20puts%20it%20neatly%20in%20the%20bag%20or%20box.%20When%20everything's%20done%2C%20she%20gets%20to%20use%20the%20debit%20card%20to%20pay%2C%20navigating%20the%20prompts%20on%20the%20screen%20like%20a%20pro.%20It's%20a%20special%20moment%20when%2C%20as%20a%20parent%2C%20you%20can%20step%20back%20and%20watch%20your%20kids%20figure%20something%20out%20on%20their%20own%20%E2%80%94%20or%20better%20yet%2C%20with%20their%20siblings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20asked%20them%20what%20they%20liked%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fself-checkout-theft-is-a-bigger-problem-than-retailers-thought-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehelping%20at%20the%20checkout%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20my%20son%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20bored.%20If%20I%20wasn't%20helping%2C%20I%20would%20just%20be%20standing%20and%20doing%20nothing%2C%20and%20it's%20boring.%26quot%3B%20It%20gives%20them%20a%20sense%20of%20purpose%20that's%20really%20fun%20to%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e8ac3b21-c3ea-438c-b3cc-a485463661d3%5C%22%3EWe've%20taken%20it%20a%20few%20steps%20further%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20created%20a%20Master%20Grocery%20List.%20It's%20laminated%2C%20so%20I%20use%20a%20dry-erase%20marker%20to%20mark%20the%20items%20we%20need%20each%20week.%20Since%20the%20kids%20have%20gotten%20more%20involved%20in%20shopping%20%E2%80%94%20and%20have%20more%20opinions%20on%20what%20they'd%20like%20to%20eat%20%E2%80%94%20I%20moved%20the%20list%20to%20a%20spot%20on%20the%20fridge%20that's%20easy%20to%20access.%20Now%2C%20if%20they%20use%20the%20last%20of%20something%2C%20realize%20they%20need%20something%20for%20school%2C%20or%20have%20a%20supper%20idea%2C%20they'll%20add%20it%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223060%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Shopping%20list%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a01fe57c9dd4cb81cda92c0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222295%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20has%20a%20laminated%20shopping%20list%20for%20the%20family.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20helping%20with%20groceries%20has%20been%20a%20theme%20in%20our%20home%20lately%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20go%20one%20step%20further%20and%20hand%20the%20phone%20to%20my%20middle%20child%20so%20she%20could%20place%20a%20pickup%20order%20herself.%20She%20had%20the%20list%20handy%2C%20and%20I%20told%20her%20the%20budget.%20She%20had%20a%20blast%20and%20did%20a%20really%20great%20job%2C%20even%20recommending%20a%20smaller%20size%20coffee%20when%20she%20saw%20the%20prices%20to%20make%20sure%20she%20stayed%20within%20the%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b7fe1154-a2fc-44b6-8f8b-5d48d5b4d90f%5C%22%3EIt%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20take%20a%20step%20back%2C%20but%20it's%20worth%20it%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20fun%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fraising-independent-kids-parenting-lessons-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eraising%20little%20humans%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20teaching%20them%20how%20to%20do%20daily%20tasks%20and%20watching%20them%20learn%20how%20to%20navigate%20the%20world.%20Basics%20like%20doing%20laundry%2C%20loading%20the%20dishwasher%2C%20and%20shopping%20take%20time%20for%20them%20to%20figure%20out%2C%20but%20they%20end%20up%20with%20a%20sense%20of%20pride%20and%20accomplishment%20as%20they%20learn.%20That%20doesn't%20mean%20it's%20always%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20time%20the%20kids%20took%20over%20at%20the%20checkout%2C%20I%20found%20myself%20reaching%20to%20help%20multiple%20times.%20But%20given%20a%20few%20extra%20seconds%2C%20they%20typically%20figured%20things%20out%20on%20their%20own.%20I'll%20still%20step%20in%20if%20necessary%2C%20but%20I%20try%20to%20wait%20for%20them%