n%20great.%20Groceries%20and%20dining%20out%20are%20noticeably%20cheaper%2C%20and%20gas%20prices%20were%20as%20low%20as%20%242.34%20per%20gallon%20before%20they%20started%20rising%20because%20of%20the%20Iran%20war.%20The%20lack%20of%20state%20income%20tax%20is%20also%20huge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20we've%20enjoyed%20those%20advantages%2C%20we've%20come%20to%20realize%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20trade-offs%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-from-austin-texas-to-new-york-city-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eliving%20in%20Texas%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20for%20us%2C%20they%20outweigh%20many%20of%20the%20benefits.%20We%20once%20thought%20living%20in%20El%20Paso%20would%20be%20a%20permanent%20relocation%2C%20but%20now%20we're%20happily%20making%20our%20way%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flived-san-francisco-austin-move-back-california-texas-tech-scene-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eback%20to%20California%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c96f8325-79cb-48dc-9b72-5f8d2f1feab3%5C%22%3ELife%20in%20Texas%20isn't%20what%20we%20thought%20it%20would%20be%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20told%20my%20family%20I%20was%20moving%20to%20El%20Paso%2C%20they%20were%20excited.%20They%20kept%20telling%20us%2C%20%26quot%3BEverything%20is%20so%20much%20cheaper%20and%20better%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20they%20were%20right%20%E2%80%94%20for%20the%20most%20part.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEl%20Paso%20really%20is%20a%20beautiful%20place%20with%20very%20kind%20people.%20It%20sits%20along%20the%20border%2C%20near%20Mexico%20and%20New%20Mexico%2C%20so%20there's%20a%20unique%20blend%20of%20cultures.%20I%20wish%20more%20people%20knew%20about%20El%20Paso's%20culture%20and%20its%20incredible%2C%20authentic%20Mexican%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228662%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20overview%20of%20the%20city%20of%20El%20Paso%2C%20Texas.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0730ff