2When%20raising%20my%20newborn%20in%20New%20York%20City%20became%20too%20difficult%2C%20I%20took%20an%20extended%20parental%20leave%20and%20moved%20to%20Berlin%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223672%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Danielle%20Elliot%20and%20her%20baby%20in%20europe%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0f70e7b1025a62a5c85c90%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222754%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20moved%20abroad%20shortly%20after%20her%20baby%20was%20born.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Danielle%20Elliot%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI%20tried%20moving%20abroad%20in%20the%20past%2C%20but%20it%20never%20worked%20out.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhen%20I%20became%20a%20new%20single%20mom%2C%20I%20struggled%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20so%20I%20headed%20to%20Berlin.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBerlin%20has%20been%20an%20incredible%20city%20for%20new%20parents.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20attempted%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fitems-i-miss-after-moving-abroad-with-family-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emove%20abroad%3C%2Fa%3E%20several%20times%2C%20even%20acquiring%20visas%2C%20but%20I%20always%20ended%20up%20back%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20decided%20to%20have%20a%20baby%20on%20my%20own%2C%20I%20put%20that%20dream%20aside.%20I%20figured%20that%20if%20I%20couldn't%20do%20it%20as%20a%20single%2030-something%2C%20it%20didn't%20seem%20feasible%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Findia-rishikesh-single-mom-relocated-kolkata-start-cafe-slow-living-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esingle%20mom%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20I%20was%20as%20surprised%20as%20anyone%20when%2C%20three%20months%20after%20having%20my%20daughter%2C%20I%20booked%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fberlin-travel-mistakes-to-avoid-first-visit%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflight%20to%20Berlin%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20haven't%20returned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223701f8b9-5847-49bf-9237-cdd60f92ee99%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaking%20a%20plan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20month%20of%20my%20daughter's%20life%20was%20a%20blur.%20I%20was%20exhausted%20and%20happy%3B%20having%20her%20felt%20like%20a%20new%20lease%20on%20life.%20I%20couldn't%20imagine%20going%20back%20to%20work%20anytime%20soon.%20I%20didn't%20really%20have%20work%20to%20go%20back%20to%20anyway%3B%20I'm%20a%20freelancer%2C%20and%20didn't%20have%20anything%20new%20lined%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20I%20received%2012%20weeks%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freaders-weigh-in-story-parental-leave-pto-reduction-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaid%20family%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20planned%20to%20look%20for%20work%20when%20that%20ended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20a%20friend%20helped%20me%20land%20a%20teaching%20job.%20That%20was%20in%20October%3B%20the%20job%20would%20start%20the%20next%20September.%20I%20decided%20I'd%20take%20care%20of%20my%20daughter%20full%20time%20until%20her%20first%20birthday%20in%20August%2C%20living%20off%20savings%2C%20and%20then%20I'd%20start%20teaching.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e34ce1ed-835c-4bd4-a989-64021e5a4954%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EChanging%20the%20plan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20loved%20my%20plan%2C%20but%20there%20were%20things%20I%20hadn't%20considered.%20First%2C%20being%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstay-at-home-mom-making-1500-weekly-from-side-hustles-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efull-time%20mom%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Brooklyn%2C%20where%20few%20people%20are%20full-time%20parents%2C%20is%20isolating.%20I%20realized%20this%20when%20my%20fellow%20new%20moms%20went%20back%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20developing%20a%20new%20identity%20is%20hard%3B%20doing%20it%20in%20the%20shadow%20of%20my%20former%20life%20felt%20even%20harder.%20With%20a%20partner%2C%20I%20might've%20been%20able%20to%20maintain%20a%20semblance%20of%20normal%20by%20taking%20turns%20leaving%20the%20house.%20As%20a%20single%20mom%2C%20this%20wasn't%20an%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20popping%20out%20for%20yoga%2C%20coffee%2C%20or%20anything.%20This%20hit%20me%20hardest%20when%20my%20daughter%20started%20falling%20asleep%20around%207%3A30%20p.m.%2C%20and%20I'd%20be%20home%20alone%20for%20the%20entire%20night%2C%20every%20night.%20Friends%20would%20come%20over%2C%20but%20by%20the%20time%20they%20got%20off%20work%2C%20I%20was%20exhausted%20and%20wanted%20to%20sleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrooklyn%20started%20to%20feel%20different.%20Trying%20to%20find%20flexible%2C%20occasional%20childcare%20proved%20too%20difficult%2C%20and%20living%20in%20a%20fourth-floor%20walkup%2C%20too%20complicated.%20When%20I%20left%20the%20stroller%20downstairs%2C%20my%20building%20superintendent%20said%20it%20would%20probably%20get%20stolen.%20I%20debated%20moving%20closer%20to%20family%2C%20but%20I%20felt%20more%20resigned%20to%20it%20than%20excited%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%20December%2C%20when%20my%20daughter%20was%20three%20months%20old%2C%20I%20changed%20my%20plan.%20If%20I%20were%20going%20to%20take%20a%20year%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-companies-maternity-parental-leave-policies%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ematernity%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I'd%20take%20it%20in%20a%20place%20where%20everyone%20takes%20it.%20I'd%20take%20it%20in%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fb383b24-7d73-4e90-aa08-fec476771abb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFinding%20childcare%20in%20Berlin%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20looked%20all%20over%20Europe%20for%20reliable%2C%20flexible%2C%20affordable%20childcare%2C%20and%20found%20a%20coworking%20spot%20with%20hourly%20day%20care%20in%20Berlin.%20It%20happened%20to%20be%20in%20the%20neighborhood%20where%20a%20friend%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20I%20could%20get%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbook-multi-city-tickets-instead-round-trip-open-jaw-flights-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eround-trip%20flight%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20Airbnb%2C%20and%20two%20hours%20of%20day%20care%20per%20day%20for%20the%20cost%20of%20my%20monthly%20rent%20in%20Brooklyn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinding%20a%20subletter%20and%20packing%20my%20apartment%20were%20easy.%20By%20then%2C%20I%20understood%20that%20babies%20don't%20need%20nearly%20as%20much%20as%20we're%20led%20to%20believe.%20I%20stayed%20home%20long%20enough%20to%20get%20my%20daughter's%20six-month%20vaccines.%20Then%2C%20with%20two%20carry-on%20suitcases%20and%20a%20stroller%2C%20we%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22634b4d88-fc22-4e02-a1dd-52d7a3c80061%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBetter%20than%20I%20dreamed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20decades%20of%20thinking%20about%20moving%20abroad%2C%20it%20was%20simple.%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-left-weekend-trip-early-kids-too-young-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebooked%20an%20Airbnb%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20crib%2C%20and%20I%20bought%20travel%20health%20insurance.%20I'm%20figuring%20out%20the%20rest%20as%20I%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBerlin%20is%20livable%20in%20a%20way%20that%20feels%20intentional.%20Many%20parents%20are%20home%20for%20the%20first%20year%2C%20so%20places%20are%20designed%20for%20parents%20and%20kids.%20When%20we%20go%20on%20walks%2C%20it's%20all%20new%20to%20me%2C%20and%20that's%20good%20for%20my%20mental%20health%2C%20as%20is%20meeting%20and%20connecting%20with%20new%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20home%2C%20I%20kept%20seeing%20what%20I%20can't%20do%20anymore%3B%20here%2C%20I%20see%20possibilities%20everywhere.%20And%20at%20night%2C%20it%20doesn't%20feel%20like%20I'm%20missing%20anything%20because%20I%20don't%20have%20anything%20to%20miss.%20I%20don't%20feel%20lonely%3B%20I%20feel%20more%20in%20tune%20with%20my%20daughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20week%20after%20arriving%2C%20the%20September%20teaching%20job%20was%20canceled%20due%20to%20budget%20cuts.%20I%20was%20disappointed%2C%20but%20soon%20saw%20this%20as%20an%20opportunity%3A%20I'm%20here%2C%20I%20like%20it%2C%20and%20now%20I%20can%20stay.%20I%20applied%20for%20a%20visa%20and%20planned%20trips%20to%20Denmark%2C%20Finland%2C%20and%20Spain%2C%20just%20to%20make%20sure%20Berlin%20really%20is%20where%20I%20want%20to%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20we're%20here%20for%20a%20year%2C%20maybe%20longer.%20For%20now%2C%20I'm%20just%20enjoying%20being%20in%20a%20new%20place%20and%20being%20here%20with%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-single-mom-left-new-york-city-moved-berlin-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1779630421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0f70f651ede568c7e172b8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-single-mom-left-new-york-city-moved-berlin-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Being%20a%20new%20single%20mom%20in%20New%20York%20City%20was%20challenging.%20When%20I%20moved%20to%20Berlin%2C%20I%20found%20a%20culture%20more%20welcoming%20to%20new%20parents.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Danielle%20Elliot)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump%20turnaround%3A%20Open%20the%20straits%2C%20close%20the%20war%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1779630223000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-131293262%2Cimgsize-116792.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftrump-turnaround-open-the-straits-close-the-war%2Farticleshow%2F131293243.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%