tre-ropes-in-iit-madras-iit-kanpur-to-help-cbse-fix-portal-glitches-126052400562_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20had%20my%20last%20child%20at%2040.%20My%20friends%20are%20in%20a%20different%20place%20than%20I%20am%2C%20but%20my%20son%20keeps%20me%20young.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221528%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%20and%20her%20son%20among%20trees.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0f200c51ede568c7e16fa8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221146%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20had%20her%20son%20at%2040.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jamie%20Davis%20Smith%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI%20had%20my%20first%20child%20at%2031%20and%20my%20fourth%20%E2%80%94%20and%20final%20%E2%80%94%20child%20at%2040.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThere%20were%20a%20few%20things%20I%20didn't%20expect%20about%20having%20a%20kid%20again%2C%20almost%2010%20years%20later.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPregnancy%20and%20delivery%20were%20surprisingly%20easy%2C%20but%20my%20friendships%20have%20suffered.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI%20always%20knew%20I%20wanted%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-family-average-summer-day-what-its-really-like-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebig%20family%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20I%20wasn't%20in%20a%20rush%20to%20get%20started.%20When%20I%20got%20married%20in%20my%20mid-20s%2C%20after%20a%20prolonged%20time%20in%20school%20earning%20two%20graduate%20degrees%2C%20I%20wasn't%20quite%20ready%20to%20have%20children.%20I%20wanted%20to%20become%20more%20established%20in%20my%20career%2C%20pay%20down%20student%20loans%2C%20and%20travel%20before%20kids%20entered%20the%20picture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20at%2031%2C%20I%20had%20my%20first%20child%2C%20followed%20quickly%20by%20two%20more.%20I%20loved%20being%20a%20mother.%20Yet%2C%20even%20with%20three%20children%20who%20were%20my%20moon%20and%20stars%2C%20I%20didn't%20feel%20as%20though%20my%20family%20was%20complete.%20It%20took%20my%20husband%20a%20few%20years%20to%20get%20on%20board%2C%20but%20we%20eventually%20agreed%20to%20grow%20our%20family%20by%20one%20more%2C%20and%20I%20had%20my%20last%20son%20just%20before%20turning%2040.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wouldn't%20change%20a%20thing%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20fully%20consider%20the%20implications%20of%20having%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbecame-mom-forties-might-never-be-a-grandma-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echild%20at%20almost%2040%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225860d218-a8b3-4274-8fc8-fdfbedac0e3c%5C%22%3EPregnancy%20and%20delivery%20went%20smoothly%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20had%20my%20son%2C%20I%20was%20ecstatic%20that%20my%20much-wanted%20fourth%20and%20final%20child%20had%20arrived.%20I%20drank%20in%20his%20newborn%20scent.%20Even%20though%20I%20was%20older%2C%20I%20found%20late-night%20wake-ups%20and%20cluster%20feeding%20easier%20and%20less%20intrusive%20than%20I%20had%20with%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplay-board-video-games-more-older-kids-than-toddlers-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eolder%20kids%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Having%20waited%20so%20long%20for%20my%20son%20and%20knowing%20he%20was%20my%20last%20made%20every%20moment%20with%20my%20baby%20seem%20just%20a%20little%20sweeter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20I%20was%20considered%20a%20%26quot%3Bgeriatric%20mother%2C%26quot%3B%20my%20pregnancy%20and%20delivery%20had%20gone%20smoothly.%20Even%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-mom-kids-miss-out-physical-activities-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E40-year-old%20mom%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20didn't%20feel%20my%20age%2C%20even%20though%20there%20was%20nearly%20a%20decade%20between%20becoming%20pregnant%20with%20my%20first%20child%20and%20giving%20birth%20to%20my%20fourth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221850%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%20and%20her%20son%20on%20a%20beach.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0f205fb1025a62a5c8598c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221388%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20wouldn't%20change%20a%20thing%20about%20becoming%20a%20mom%20again%20at%2040.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jamie%20Davis%20Smith%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225b4a66d8-65e4-4adf-9adf-7a2225314e6b%5C%22%3EMy%20friendships%20suffered%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%2C%20logically%2C%20that%20being%20an%20older%20mom%20would%20have%20its%20challenges.%20However%2C%20I%20didn't%20fully%20understand%20the%20implications%2C%20and%20they%20didn't%20become%20apparent%20until%20my%20son%20was%20a%20little%20older.%20By%20the%20time%20I%20had%20my%20last%20child%2C%20most%20of%20my%20friends%20had%20their%20days%20free%20outside%20of%20work.%20They%20were%20regularly%20getting%20together%20for%20coffee%20breaks%2C%20lunch%20dates%2C%20and%20dinners%20out.%20Although%20bringing%20a%20baby%20along%20was%20usually%20possible%20and%20often%20welcome%2C%20once%20he%20became%20a%20mobile%2C%20chatty%20toddler%2C%20I%20had%20to%20decline%20more%20invitations.%20My%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchoosing-not-to-have-kids-has-made-friendships-more-challenging-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efriendships%20suffered%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20now%2C%20years%20after%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoungest-graduating-elementary-school-wish-done-things-differently-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eson%20started%20school%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20find%20it%20hard%20to%20relate%20to%20many%20of%20my%20friends'%20lives.%20While%20I%20am%20still%20in%20the%20thick%20of%20raising%20an%20elementary-school-aged%20child%2C%20they%20are%20no%20longer%20making%20school%20lunches%2C%20chauffeuring%20their%20kids%20to%20sports%20practice%2C%20and%20looking%20over%20homework%20every%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20most%20of%20my%20friends%20still%20have%20children%20at%20home%2C%20their%20kids%20are%20largely%20self-sufficient%2C%20leaving%20them%20with%20the%20kind%20of%20free%20time%20I%20can%20only%20dream%20about.%20Last%20year%2C%20some%20friends%20planned%20a%20girls'%20trip%2C%20but%20I%20declined%20to%20go%20because%20it%20would%20be%20difficult%20to%20leave%20my%20son%20for%20so%20long.%20My%20friends%20understood%20but%20went%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Th%20eauthor%20and%20her%20son%20on%20an%20open-air%20vehicle.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0f209d7ff506e273e661b1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20found%20a%20few%20things%20about%20having%20a%20child%20at%2040%20to%20be%20different%20from%20having%20a%20child%20at%2031.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jamie%20Davis%20Smith%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227b596df2-aea7-4a10-9c5e-afd72ebb2f6a%5C%22%3EMy%20son%20keeps%20me%20young%2C%20but%20I%20worry%20constantly%20about%20not%20being%20around%20for%20him%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20that%20having%20a%20child%20in%20elementary%20school%20keeps%20me%20active%20and%20engaged.%20We%20still%20go%20ice%20skating%20together%2C%20and%20unlike%20my%20teenagers%2C%20my%20youngest%20actually%20wants%20to%20tell%20me%20about%20his%20day%20and%20snuggle%20on%20the%20sofa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20I%20worry%20constantly%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-parents-aging-anxiety-challenges-benefits-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20being%20around%3C%2Fa%3E%20long%20enough%20for%20my%20son%20as%20he%20grows%20up%20and%20starts%20his%20own%20family.%20I%20sometimes%20mourn%20the%20relationship%20I%20will%20never%20have%20with%20his%20children%20and%20feel%20sad%20that%20my%20grandchildren%20probably%20won't%20have%20grandparents%20around%20to%20spoil%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20own%20parents%20were%20so%20supportive%20of%20me%20when%20I%20started%20my%20family%20and%20never%20hesitated%20to%20step%20in%20to%20help.%20They%20shower%20my%20kids%20with%20love.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20my%20age%2C%20it's%20unlikely%20I%20will%20be%20able%20to%20do%20the%20same%20for%20my%20children%20and%20grandchildren%20for%20very%20long%2C%20particularly%20for%20my%20youngest%20son.%20Although%20I%20knew%20a%20more%20limited%20time%20together%20was%20a%20reality%20when%20I%20decided%20to%20have%20a%20child%20at%20nearly%2040%2C%20I%20feel%20the%20loss%20more%20acutely%2C%20seeing%20how%20quickly%20time%20is%20speeding%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2269d3d1f0-12c6-4a00-9af0-849b3a2eef97%5C%22%3EI%20still%20wouldn't%20change%20a%20thing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20I%20keep%20being%20surprised%20by%20the%20implications%20of%20having%20a%20baby%20later%20in%20life%2C%20I%20don't%20regret%20a%20thing.%20With%20his%20late%20arrival%2C%20my%20son%20completed%20our%20family.%20He%20brings%20my%20entire%20family%20so%20much%20joy%2C%20and%20it's%20hard%20to%20imagine%20life%20without%20him.%20There%20are%20also%20advantages%20to%20having%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhad-kids-later-made-friends-younger-moms-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echild%20later%20in%20life%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20are%20more%20financially%20stable%2C%20I%20have%20more%20perspective%20on%20what%20truly%20matters%2C%20and%20he%20keeps%20me%20young%20at%20heart.%20All%20of%20this%20helps%20me%20enjoy%20motherhood%20a%20little%20more%20than%20I%20did%20with%20my%20older%20kids%2C%20who%20were%20born%20when%20I%20was%20younger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-mom-pregnancy-easy-friendships-changed-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1779628201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insid