ere%20on%20display%20this%20week%20during%20the%20annual%20SOF%20Week%20conference%20in%20Tampa%2C%20Florida%2C%20a%20major%20gathering%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreen-berets-testing-drones-that-can-slip-past-enemy-sensors-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Especial%20operations%3C%2Fa%3E%20service%20members%20and%20defense%20industry%20representatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20other%20items%20on%20display%20that%20Kelly's%20team%20is%20looking%20at%20possibly%20having%20service%20members%20test%20included%20suppressors%20to%20reduce%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-force-interest-in-camo-nets-to-block-thermal-imaging-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eheat%20signatures%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20biometric%20devices%20to%20prevent%20swim%20deaths.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20ballistic%20cap%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a109e077ff506e273e66c4a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20design%20for%20a%20ballistic%20cover%20for%20troops.%3Cp%3EKelsey%20Baker%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EManufactured%20by%20R-12%2C%20the%20ballistic%20ball%20caps%20were%20created%20by%20a%20surgeon.%20They%20include%20patrol%20caps%20%E2%80%94%20known%20within%20the%20military%20as%20%26quot%3Bcovers%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20that%20soldiers%20and%20Marines%20wear%20with%20their%20camouflage%20uniforms%2C%20as%20well%20as%20neutral-colored%20ball%20caps%20many%20special%20operations%20members%20are%20known%20to%20favor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20ballistic%20cap%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a10af44b1025a62a5c865a0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAnother%20ballistic%20patrol%20cap%20design%3Cp%3EKelsey%20Baker%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20protective%20caps%20could%20also%20be%20worn%20by%20law%20enforcement%20officers%20or%20by%20personnel%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20federal%20government%20where%20workers%20could%20be%20exposed%20to%20harm%2C%20Kelly%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20R-12%2C%20the%20protective%20hat%20%26quot%3Bwill%20slow%20the%20energy%20of%20NIJ%20Level%20IIIA%20threats%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20designation%20that%20applies%20to%20powerful%20ammunition%20fired%20from%20handguns%2C%20though%20it%20does%20not%20protect%20against%20ammunition%20fired%20from%20rifles%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Institute%20of%20Justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20manufacturer%20said%20that%20in%20a%20shooting%20scenario%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20kinetic%20energy%20of%20the%20bullet%20may%20still%20damage%20the%20skull%20and%2For%20cause%20bruising%2C%20bleeding%2C%20or%20swelling%20in%20the%20brain.%20However%2C%20those%20injuries%20are%20treatable%20and%20survivable%20with%20prompt%20surgical%20care.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENational%20Guard%20units%2C%20including%20the%20West%20Virginia%20National%20Guard%2C%20have%20expressed%20particular%20interest%20in%20the%20gear%2C%20Kelly%20said%2C%20following%20the%20deadly%20shooting%20attack%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20last%20November%20in%20which%20two%20service%20members%20from%20the%20West%20Virginia%20National%20Guard%20were%20attacked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpc.%20Sarah%20Beckstrom%20died%20from%20a%20gunshot%20wound%20to%20the%20back%20of%20the%20head.%20A%20second%20service%20member%2C%20Staff%20Sgt.%20Andrew%20Wolfe%2C%20was%20also%20shot%20in%20the%20head%20and%20seriously%20wounded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ball%20caps%20weigh%2011%20ounces%20and%20cost%20%24365%20each%2C%20and%20they%20should%20be%20replaced%20every%20two%20years%2C%20according%20to%20R-12.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fa-pentag